OL,7,FDES, originally called
OL,8,FDiethylstilboestrol, is a synthetic
OL,9,Foestrogen invented in Britain in 1939.
OL,10,FResearch suggests pregnant women who
OL,11,Ftook DES may have a 30% higher risk of
OL,12,Fbreast cancer.
OL,14,FTheir daughters, known as DES
OL,15,Fdaughters, exposed in the womb, are at
OL,16,Fan increased risk of clear cell cancer
OL,17,Fof the cervix and vagina, which is not
OL,18,Fpicked up by routine screening.
